            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.8.34" />
               <note type="curatorial">Seymour Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">34</fw>
<opener>
<dateline>Sept. 11, '22.</dateline>

<salute>Dear Seymour:_</salute>
</opener>
<p>On the second page of my reply to your Hattie letter, this sentence occurs: "Since then I have written but one lyric which appeared in Century". For this sentence, substitute the following, if you decide to print the thing anywhere: "Since then I have written nothing for magazine publication.<del/> This, I find, is the fact, the lyric mentioned having been written before the time <add>stated.</add> <del/></p>

<p>I didn't tell you in my unofficial letter of the other day that Hattie and I got into a row very soon after POETRY started. The row began as soon as I saw which way  she was blowing. I think it was that ass, Ezry, who cooled my ardor. After that the braying was deafening, and my love never returned.</p>
<closer>
<salute>Yours,</salute>

<signed>J.G.N.</signed>
</closer>                
<postscript><p>When <hi rend="underline">Poetry</hi> was started, the lady gave me every opportunity to become immortal, but the row was fatal.</p></postscript>
</div1>
